> Balsamic vinegar is fantastic in more than just salads. It has rich notes that lend
> themselves brilliantly to a wide array of uses. In this recipe, jammy caramelized
> onions are simmered in the deep brown liquid, becoming meltingly tender. When spooned
> over chicken breasts, they seem to infuse each bite with juiciness and tangy flavor.
> Few toppings are capable of elevating a classic meal of meat, potatoes, and veg so far
> beyond the ordinary.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Core and finely
chop @Roma tomato{1}. Remove and discard tough stems and ribs from
@kale{4%oz}; roughly chop leaves. Chop @garlic{2%clove}. Cut
@Yukon Gold potatoes{12%oz} into 1-inch cubes and place in a medium #pot{} with
enough water to cover by 2 inches.

Bring potatoes to a boil. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup
cooking water, then drain and return to pot. Mash to desired consistency using a
#potato masher{}. Stir in @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, @sour cream{4%tbsp}, and
@butter{1%tbsp}. (TIP: If needed, add cooking water 1-2 TBSP at a time to create a creamy
consistency.) Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover pot and set aside.

== Onion Jam and Chicken ==

Meanwhile, heat another @butter{1%tbsp} and a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a medium pan
over medium heat (we used nonstick). Add onion, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of
salt and pepper. Cook, tossing occasionally, until softened, about ~{10%minutes}.
Increase heat to medium high. Stir in tomato, @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, and ⅓ cup
tap water. Cook until jammy, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper; set aside.

While onion cooks, pat @chicken breasts{12%oz} dry with a paper towel. Season all over
with plenty of salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan
over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until no longer pink in center, about
~{6-8%minutes} per side. Transfer to pan with onion jam. Keep covered off heat until
ready to serve.

== Garlicky Kale ==

Place kale and 1 TBSP tap water in a large #microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover bowl with
#plastic wrap{}. Microwave on high until tender, about ~{3%minutes}. Carefully remove
wrap. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in large pan used for chicken over medium-high
heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Toss in kale and any
liquid in bowl. Cook until liquid evaporates, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Season kale with salt and pepper. Divide mashed potatoes, kale, and chicken between
plates. Spoon onion jam over chicken and serve.